tweet:
When a autistic person flaps their hands or rocks or repeats words this is called stimming, 
There are many different types of stims,
Stims serve many beneficial functions including emotional self regulation and expression,
Stimming is absolutely NOT a meaningless behaviour.

tweet:
When a autistic person flaps their hands or rocks or repeats words  this is called stimming,
There are many different types of stims,
Stims serve many beneficial functions including emotional self regulation and expression,
Stimming is absolutely not a meaningless behaviour.

tweet: To be clear I am talking about people who openly admit to wearing/purchasing  a sunflower lanyard as a excuse not to wear a facemask, I am absolutely not talking about people with genuine hidden disabilities.

tweet: @PaulRidley5 I understand,  let's be clear the tweet is intended for those people that openly admit to using the lanyard as a excuse not to wear a facemask it is not intended to discriminate people with hidden disabilities,  sadly there are people wearing them to avoid wearing a facemask

name: Autism care and share
description: I'm Adam | Proud Father of 3 | Full Time Carer |My Eldest Son Ryan is autistic.
tweet:
Sunflower lanyards are for people with hidden disabilities such as hearing loss, sight loss, and autism they are intended as a discreet way of showing that the person may need extra support .
They were never intended to be used for people that refuse to wear a face mask.

Put the batteries in

tweet:
